  "prompt": "If I consumed 1 pint of alcohol, for 5 days in a row, but stopped 4 to 5 days before an etg test will I pass?",
  "response": "Ethyl glucuronide (EtG) tests are quite sensitive and can detect alcohol consumption for up to 80 hours after ingestion. A pint of alcohol is a significant amount, and consuming that amount for several consecutive days increases the likelihood that EtG will be present in your system for a longer period.\n\nConsidering you've stopped drinking 4 to 5 days before the test, you might be very close to the detection window. While you might pass the test, there's a substantial risk that the EtG could still be detectable.\n\nSeveral factors can influence the detection window, including your metabolism, overall health, age, weight, and how much alcohol you've consumed overall. The safest course of action is to abstain from alcohol for at least 80 hours (and ideally longer) before taking an EtG test to ensure a negative result.\n\nNonetheless, there is no exact guarantee as every individual's body processes alcohol differently. If needed, consulting a medical professional for personalized advice might provide more clarity.",
